values:
So, since I last posted, I met w/ my chair again.&nbsp; He told me basically what I already knew: that I had to start emailing labs.&nbsp; 

So I did that.&nbsp; I'm looking mostly in the biology department downtown because (1) chemistry is not my strong suit any more (it's sad to say), (2) chemistry doesn't have people doing biophysics so much, (3) biochemistry uptown only has 2 or 3 professors who interest me.&nbsp; 

Not that most of you know who these people are, but for the few of you who do, I'm looking at either Hunt, Yang, Tong, Sheetz, or Dr. X (a professor whose name I don't know, but apparently he works on the 6th floor of Fairchild and is brand new and works on Chromatin).&nbsp; Do y'all have any suggestions/know anyone who is in these labs whom I can chat with? I'm also looking in biochem at Palmer and maybe Shapiro--and MAYBE in chemistry at Gonzalez (but that's doubtful).&nbsp; 

Also, I'll be downtown tomorrow around lunch time (11am apt w/ Yang; 1:30 w/ Tong--if anyone wants to grab lunch....)

So, that's going as can be hoped, I guess.

In other news, I went to El Mundo (this ghetto-looking clothing store on 134th street &amp; broadway) b/c I heard they had some good deals on clothing.&nbsp; And they do.&nbsp; I got some quality shirts--like Kenneth Cole and BCBG--for $15 each.&nbsp; I got a Diesel Tshirt for $6 which I'm giving away as a present--I couldn't fit into it if I tried...stupid boyfriend being the best cook ever....&nbsp; 

BF and I also made brunch for my friend Nancy and her daughter on Sunday after going out on Saturday night to Red Bamboo (fantastic vegetarian restaurant on W4th and 6th) and then to the Boiler room (crappy gay bar--w/ realllly cheap drinks--$3 wells)&nbsp; 

A friend of the BFs came back from Israel yesterday--and her flight to TX got cancelled b/c of the snow, so she crashed here and made TONS of noise and was a generally rude houseguest.&nbsp; Such is life, I guess.&nbsp; Luckily, she was gone by 7am.&nbsp; 

BF's now at work--he officially got offered the job--so that's great news--and yet he still has no leads on an apartment.&nbsp; Sigh.&nbsp; 

Anyway--today is laundry and cleaning until 5pm when I meet w/ Dr. Hunt downtown.&nbsp; Oh, and reading this awesomely cool NMR book I have.

But...

did any of you see Desperate Housewives last night? Oh my goodness! I'm still thinking about it!&nbsp;&nbsp; 

And, Brothers and Sisters was quite disappointing--a filler episode if I've ever seen one.&nbsp; And no gay kissing in this one, sadly.
